Wrapper Class
============================================================
Wrapper classes are the predefined class in Java which can contain primitive data type. In simple words
we can wrap a primitive value to wrapper class.

Primitive Type				Wrapper Class
--------------------------------------------
boolean						Boolean
byte						Byte
int							Integer
short						Short
long						Long
float						Float
double						Double
char						Character


***Facts***
1. int a=100;
   -- a is a variable, int is data type and 100 is value of a
2. Integer b=200;
   -- b is a reference/object of Integer class with value 200
   
   
********INTERVIEW QUESTION********
1. What is parent class of all the wrapper classes?
  -- For boolean and character> Object Class
  -- For byte, int, short, long, float, double> Number Class

2. When to use the wrapper class?
  -- While using collection framework
  -- To convert object to primitive data type
  -- To convert primitive data type to object
  -- Many libraries (Selenium, SpringBoot) in Java deal with objects, not primitive data types